Program: The Why Factor
Title: Wine
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswrl1
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 18 Dec 2018
Wine has been referred to as the nectar of the gods, and has been tempting connoisseurs for centuries. But contained in this simple pleasure is an incredibly complex product; and anyone interested in reaching the pinnacle of the wine world must learn more about what goes into every wine bottle than most of us will ever take the time to know. In this edition of the Why Factor on the BBC World Service, Sandra Kanthal speaks to experts of the wine trade to find out why there is so much to discover from a bottle of wine. Image: Wine being poured (Credit: Getty Images) Show less